Two men, thought to be part of a gang of house robbers were arrested earlier this afternoon by quick-thinking cops at Sheppie shopping centre, South Coast Herald reports. Cops on the scene. During a crime intelligence operation, driven by Margate Intelligence Unit, police spotted a suspicious vehicle (a gold Toyota Corolla) at a shopping centre in Port Shepstone. As soon as the gang of four realised they were being followed by the long arm of the law, two of the men jumped out of the vehicle and fled on foot. READ MORE: Criminals target domestic workers, warn police Police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Zandra Wiid said the other two men were however arrested and are currently in police custody. Police found that the Corolla s registration plates were false. They also recovered house breaking implements, gloves and balaclavas inside the vehicle. It is suspected the men had been involved in house-break-ins on the South Coast. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. &nbsp;